<item>
            <title>[CAMEL-1332] StreamCachingInterceptor can be enabled both as a strategy and as an interceptor -- should only be a strategy</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CAMEL-1332</link>
                <project id="12311211" key="CAMEL">Camel</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Right now, there are two ways of enabling stream caching:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;explicitly enable it through the DSL&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;implicitly enable it through e.g. a Multicast or DeadletterChannel&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;We should make that a single way of enablement or else document the rationale for the difference properly.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12486852">CAMEL-1332</key>
            <summary>StreamCachingInterceptor can be enabled both as a strategy and as an interceptor -- should only be a strategy</summary>
